    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "CHEF'S SUGGESTION\nYum Makeua Yao\n(Thai Green Aubergine Salad)\nINGREDIENTS\nfresh green aubergine\nBoiled prawns\nBoiled egg wedge\n20\ngrams x 8 pieces\ngramsao preces\npieces\nDRESSING\nFish sauce\nFresh lime juice\nBrown sugar\nJuice of pickled garlic\nCrushed red chilli\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\nGARNISH\nShallot, peeled, sliced\nRed chilli, julienned\n16\nCoriander leaves\nPickled garlic (Kratiem dong)\nGround dried shrimp\n40\n80*\ngrams\nHOW TO PREPARE\n- To make the dressing, combine all the ingredients together and\nstir until the brown sugar has dissolved, set aside.\n- Grill over charcoal, moderate heat and\nremove the skin of\ngreen aubergine, cut into 1 inches long and cut them in quarter\nlengthwise, then place on serving dish.\n- For serving : Pour dressing as preferable over green aubergine\nand layer with sliced shallot, ground dried shrimp, and garnish with\negg wedge, boiled prawns, julienne of red chilli.\nNote : For those who prefer more or less spicy taste, can adjust\nchilli as require.\nTG 992 Y - FEB/MAY / AUG/NOV\n2007.08:135",
      "CHEF'S SUGGESTION\nYum Makeua Yao\n(Thai Green Aubergine Salad)\nINGREDIENTS\nFresh green aubergine\nBoiled prawns\nBoiledegg wedge\n50\n20\n16\ngrams x 8 pieces\ngrams x 8 pieces\npreces\nDRESSING\nFish sauce\nFresh lime juice\nBrown sugar\nJuice of pickled garlic\nGrushed red chilli\n80\n60\n30.\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\nGARNISH\nShallot, peeled, sliced\nRed chilli, julienned\n40\n16\nCoriander leaves\nPickled garlic (Kratiem dong)\nGround dried shrimp\n40\n80\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\ngrams\nHOW TO PREPARE\n- To make the dressing, combine all the ingredients together and\nstir until the brown sugar has dissolved, set aside.\n- Grill over charcoal, moderate heat and remove the skin of\ngreen aubergine, cut into 1f inches long and cut them in quarter\nlengthwise, then place on serving dish.\n- For serving : Pour dressing as preferable over green aubergine\nand layer with sliced shallot, ground dried shrimp, and garnish with\negg wedge, boiled prawns, julienne of red chilli.\nNote : For those who prefer more or less spicy taste, can adjust\nchilli as require.\nTG 992 Y - FEB/MAY/AUG/NOV\n2007.086:135"
